          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The radioactive  11Li beam was produced in",
                "fragmentation reactions using a primary 18O beam",
                "from  the heavy-ion synchrotron, SIS. The secondary",
                "11Li beam, with an energy of 280  MeV/u, was selected",
                "by magnetic analysis in the fragment separator, FRS,",
                "and directed  towards a liquid hydrogen  target placed",
                "in front of the large-gap dipole magnet, ALADIN,",
                "and the large-area  neutron detector, LAND.",
                "The 11Li beam intensity was ~ 50 ions/s."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The liquid hydrogen was kept in a container (30 mm in",
                "diameter and  50 mm long) with thin  mylar windows",
                "and placed in a vacuum chamber. The target thickness",
                "was 350 mg/cm2.  Background measurements were",
                "performed with  an empty container."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP",
                "LONGC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " large-gap dipole magnet spectrometer",
                "ALADIN and the large area neutron detector LAND"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWDC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The polar and azimuthal angles of the",
                "trajectories of the reaction  fragments were measured",
                " with two multi-wire-proportional-chambers, MWPC"
              ]
            }
          ],
